# Agent Instructions

## Validation

- `make lint` — run often during development
- `make check` — run before considering work done
- `make quality` — run before marking work complete
- Prefer `nix develop path:. --command make check` so required tools come from `flake.nix`

## Code Conventions

- Reference `internal/seed/` for package layout and idiomatic examples
- Prefer the standard library unless a focused dependency clearly helps
- Return wrapped errors with context; avoid sentinel strings
- Use structured logging (`log/slog` or equivalent), not print logging
- No dead code, unchecked errors, package globals, or `init()` functions

## Testing

- Keep tests table-driven where cases share behavior
- Cover happy paths, error paths, and boundary values
- Use real assertions; avoid tautologies and empty tests
- Mock at process boundaries, not internal helper functions
- Run coverage before CRAP analysis so `coverage.out` is fresh

## What Lint Catches Automatically

Don't worry about these — lint will catch them:
- File and function length limits
- Exported declaration organization
- Placeholder comments and print logging
- Security issues, unchecked errors, and non-exhaustive switches
